cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.RO, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a method for using language as an abstraction for hierarchical reinforcement learning, which involves learning concepts and sub-skills that can be composed to solve longer tasks. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of language also involves natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also introduces an object interaction environment, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV).
